title: For Sale:  One SKS and parts toward another sks
postcontent: One complete SKS rifle with grenade launcher, with a very nice blood-red wooden stock, and then an additional barrel and receiver already mated/assembled that looks like it has not been issued, or at least used very little, then a lot of other parts as you can see in the picture. Basically giving it all away at $210.00. That is obviously my bottom dollar.  I'm cleaning house and selling most of my firearms. I've moved a lot of them already.So here is the story: you gotta know something about the SKS or don't buy this. It is not ready to shoot. The one complete rifle I assembled months ago and took it out shooting and it worked and then the last round I shot through it, it tore the rim off the 7.62 round and threw hot powder in my face. I thanked Jesus for letting me keep my retinas, as I had my eyewear on. I then retired the rifle and did some research. Some websites said that incorrect headspace (distance between the bolt face when closed and the rear of the 7.62 round) can cause this to happen. Other websites said oversized headspace just reduces accuracy and cannot hurt anything nor cause the failure at the range that I had. Anyway, I checked the headspace with a way suggested on the web (stacking 3 pieces of tape on the back of a loaded 7.62 round, and the bolt shouldn't go all the way forward to the point of locking) but mine did, indicating too many thousandths of an inch between the closed bolt and the back of the chambered round. Anyway, other sites said a dirty chamber will snag the brass and let the bolt pull the rim off of the round when fired...and that the problem indeed is no't headspace. I don't know if headspace causes this or not, but I know this rifle failed the tape test from the internet, and that a rim was pulled off one time when I fired it....that was enough for me to put it down. I've.never adjusted headspace on a rifle.The stock is beautiful and there are a lot of parts here, including the complete rifle; it's a steal if you want to fool with it. I'm selling about every gun I own, so I don't want to fool with it. I'm taking about 150 dollar loss on this, but so be it. I won't travel to give my guns away of course, you have to come to me in Graham, or in Burlington or Elon during the workday Monday thru Friday, for this price.I will answer emails in the order that they come. I don't expect to have this package for long at $210.00
